			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Isn't there a way to "synthesize cheaply" the whole MMC5 chip ?  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt=":roll:" title="Rolling Eyes" /> <br />I mean this chip is over 20 years old and technology has advanced....</div>
<br />CPLDs are cheap, but the ones designed to work in a 5.0 V environment are either much smaller (e.g. 36 to 72 macrocells) or far more expensive. FPGAs generally need a CPLD to load them at power-on. This takes time, and the CPU needs to have the reset vector yesterday. ASICs are dirt cheap in quantity, but the first unit is cost prohibitive for a hobbyist to make.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

